-- Brazil to Boost Foreigners' Fixed-Income Investment Tax to 6% to Cool Real
-- B y   A n d r e   S o l i a n i
-- 2010-10-18T20:57:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-18/brazil-to-increase-foreigners-fixed-income-investment-tax-to-6-from-4-.html
Brazil Finance Minister Guido
Mantega said the country will increase a tax on foreigners’
investments in fixed-income securities to 6 percent from 4
percent.  The tax on foreign investors’ margin deposits for futures
markets will climb to 6 percent from 0.38 percent, Mantega told
reporters today in Sao Paulo.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andre Soliani in Brasilia at 
 asoliani@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
